Why wrap your head around complicated kadane logic?

Whenever you see finding subarrays that meet a certain criteria, prefix sums should be the first thing that jump to your head.

How does prefix sums work? 
You just keep a running sum of the array.
You subtract previous runningsums from the current running sum to get your desired sub array.

So to get the maximum subarray at any given point, you subtract the minimum running sum from the current running sum.

```
class Solution {
    public int maxSubArray(int[] nums) {
        int min = 0;

        int runningSum = 0;

        int max = nums[0];
        for (int num: nums) {
            runningSum += num;
            max = Math.max(max, runningSum - min);
            min = Math.min(runningSum, min);
        }
        return max;
    }
}
```

I also have an prefix sum explanation for the Maximum product subarray
https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-product-subarray/discuss/843820/Say-goodbye-to-Kadane-hello-to-intuitive-O(n)-prefix-sum-solution-Java

